Function Reference/comment excerpt « WordPress Codex
-----------

Displays an excerpt (maximum of 20 words) of a comment's text.

Use
[get\_comment\_excerpt](/index.php?title=Template_Tags/get_comment_excerpt&action=edit&redlink=1 "Template Tags/get comment excerpt (page does not exist)")
to retrieve the value.

Usage
-----

`  <?php comment_excerpt( $comment_ID ); ?> `

Example
-------

    <p>Latest comment: <?php comment_excerpt(); ?></p>

Parameters
----------

 `comment_ID` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The ID of the comment for which to print the excerpt.
    Default: 0 (the current comment)

Filters
-------

[apply\_filters()](/Function_Reference/apply_filters "Function Reference/apply filters")
Calls 'comment\_excerpt' hook before displaying excerpt

Changelog
---------

-    ? : Added the 'comment\_ID' parameter.
-   Since: 1.2.0

